                "id": "a6fb7b2d-d597-45a8-8682-8844c2bb7fff"
              }
            ],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Sabemos o básico sobre como o frontend e o backend se comunicam. Agora podemos começar a construir nosso servidor web com Express.</p><img src=\"a6fb7b2d-d597-45a8-8682-8844c2bb7fff\" visible-if=\"always\" /></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "require()",
            "id": 121535,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Para usar o Express, nós <em>requeremos</em> ele em nosso código usando a função <code>require</code> embutida do Node.</p><p>Normalmente, atribuímos a saída de <code>require</code> a uma variável com o mesmo nome do pacote que estamos usando.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"13\" /><option startIndex=\"16\" endIndex=\"23\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"node\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>express</code> seguido de <code>require</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Express App",
            "id": 122143,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Vamos criar um aplicativo Express. Vamos começar criando uma variável chamada <code>app</code>.</p><p>Dentro da variável, vamos então armazenar a saída da função <code>express</code> embutida do Express.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"36\" endIndex=\"41\" /><option startIndex=\"42\" endIndex=\"45\" /><option startIndex=\"46\" endIndex=\"47\" /><option startIndex=\"48\" endIndex=\"55\" /><option startIndex=\"55\" endIndex=\"56\" /><option startIndex=\"56\" endIndex=\"57\" /><option startIndex=\"57\" endIndex=\"58\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>const</code> seguido de <code>app</code> e depois <code>=</code>, <code>express</code>, <code>(</code>, <code>)</code>, <code>;</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Express Server",
            "id": 121537,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Criamos o <code>app</code>, mas ele não está fazendo nada no momento. Vamos fazer com que ele escute as requisições recebidas.</p><p>Para fazer isso, usaremos a função <code>listen</code> embutida do Express.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"app.listen();\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"60\" endIndex=\"63\" /><option startIndex=\"63\" endIndex=\"64\" /><option startIndex=\"64\" endIndex=\"70\" /><option startIndex=\"70\" endIndex=\"71\" /><option startIndex=\"71\" endIndex=\"72\" /><option startIndex=\"72\" endIndex=\"73\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>app</code> seguido de <code>.</code> e depois <code>listen</code>, <code>(</code>, <code>)</code>, <code>;</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Two Parameters",
            "id": 121749,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>A função <code>listen</code> recebe dois parâmetros. O primeiro parâmetro especifica o <strong>número da porta</strong>.</p><p>O segundo parâmetro é uma <strong>callback function</strong> que é executada quando o servidor inicia.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"app.listen(\" /><text value=\"3000\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", () =&gt; {});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"71\" endIndex=\"75\" /><option startIndex=\"77\" endIndex=\"85\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>3000</code> seguido de <code>() =&gt; {}</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "What is a Port?*",
            "id": 121540,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>O número da porta é um identificador distinto que informa ao servidor qual aplicação deve processar uma solicitação recebida.</p><p>As portas permitem que múltiplas aplicações se conectem a um servidor simultaneamente com diferentes requisições HTTP.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"app.listen(\" /><text value=\"3000\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", () =&gt; {});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"71\" endIndex=\"75\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"function\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>3000</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Port Number Variable",
            "id": 121538,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>É prática comum atribuir o número da porta a uma variável e, em seguida, passar essa variável para a função <code>listen</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" port = \" /><text value=\"3000\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"app.listen(port, () =&gt; {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(\" /><text value=\"`Server is running on port \" /><text value=\"${port}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"65\" endIndex=\"69\" /><option startIndex=\"72\" endIndex=\"76\" /><option startIndex=\"90\" endIndex=\"94\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"gateway\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Server is running on port 3000\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>port</code> seguido de <code>3000</code> e finalmente <code>port</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Console Log",
            "id": 121753,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Quando o servidor começa a escutar a porta especificada, a função de callback é acionada.</p><p>Vamos usar a função de callback para exibir o número da porta no console.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" express = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;express&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" app = express();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" port = \" /><text value=\"3000\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"app.listen(port, () =&gt; {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(\" /><text value=\"`Server is running on port \" /><text value=\"${port}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"96\" endIndex=\"101\" /><option startIndex=\"106\" endIndex=\"117\" /><option startIndex=\"147\" endIndex=\"151\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Server is running on port 3000\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>() =&gt;</code> seguido de <code>console.log</code> e finalmente <code>port</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
